      "content": "Manuka honey is excellent, but for a cut that won't fully stop bleeding, you need immediate, decisive action. Slathering it on is fine, but you must also apply a very tight, conforming bandage over the honey to maintain pressure and prevent further leakage. If the bleeding persists despite firm pressure and honey application, you need to get it checked out because that could indicate a deeper vessel issue that honey alone can't fix.",
      "source": "target",
